{
  "page": "Battle at Rook's Rest",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table style=\"margin: 4px 10%; border: 1px solid #aaa; background:#fbfbfb;\"><tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"padding: 2px 0 2px 0.5em;border-left: 10px solid #1e90ff;\">\n<div style=\"width: 50px;\"><img alt=\"Mbox notice.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/40px-Mbox_notice.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/60px-Mbox_notice.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/80px-Mbox_notice.png 2x\" />\n</div></td><td style=\"border: none; padding: 0.25em 0.9em; width: 100%;\"> <b>Note:</b> The title of this article is conjecture and may be subject to change.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background: #B0C4DE; text-align:center;\">Battle at Rook's Rest</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:The_Batle_at_Rook%27s_Rest_by_Jordi_Gonzales_Escamilla.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"The Batle at Rook&#39;s Rest by Jordi Gonzales Escamilla.jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/ba/The_Batle_at_Rook%27s_Rest_by_Jordi_Gonzales_Escamilla.jpg/400px-The_Batle_at_Rook%27s_Rest_by_Jordi_Gonzales_Escamilla.jpg\" width=\"400\" height=\"333\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/ba/The_Batle_at_Rook%27s_Rest_by_Jordi_Gonzales_Escamilla.jpg/600px-The_Batle_at_Rook%27s_Rest_by_Jordi_Gonzales_Escamilla.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/ba/The_Batle_at_Rook%27s_Rest_by_Jordi_Gonzales_Escamilla.jpg/800px-The_Batle_at_Rook%27s_Rest_by_Jordi_Gonzales_Escamilla.jpg 2x\" /></a><div><div style=\"width:100%; border-bottom: 1px solid #aaa;\"><a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II Targaryen</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Sunfyre\" title=\"Sunfyre\">Sunfyre</a> are badly injured by <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aemon)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Aemon)\">Rhaenys Targaryen</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Meleys\" title=\"Meleys\">Meleys</a>, as depicted by Jordi Gonzales Escamilla in <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>.</div></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Conflict</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Date</th><td>\nlate <a href=\"/index.php/129_AC\" title=\"129 AC\">129&#160;AC</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Place</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Rook%27s_Rest\" title=\"Rook&#39;s Rest\">Rook's Rest</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Result</th><td>\nVictory for the <a href=\"/index.php/Greens\" title=\"Greens\">greens</a></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<table style=\"width:100%; text-align:left;\">\n<tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center;\"><b>Combatants</b></td></tr><tr><td width=\"50%\" style=\"border-right:1px dotted #aaa;\"><a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\"><img alt=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/5f/Rhaenyra_Targaryen.svg/32px-Rhaenyra_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"32\" height=\"35\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/5f/Rhaenyra_Targaryen.svg/48px-Rhaenyra_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/5f/Rhaenyra_Targaryen.svg/64px-Rhaenyra_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <b><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">House Targaryen</a>/<a href=\"/index.php/Blacks\" title=\"Blacks\">Blacks</a></b>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Staunton\" title=\"House Staunton\"><img alt=\"House Staunton.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/9e/House_Staunton.svg/20px-House_Staunton.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/9e/House_Staunton.svg/30px-House_Staunton.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/9/9e/House_Staunton.svg/40px-House_Staunton.svg.png 2x\" /></a>&#160;<a href=\"/index.php/House_Staunton\" title=\"House Staunton\">House Staunton</a></li></ul></td>\n    <td width=\"50%\"><a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\"><img alt=\"Aegon II Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/e1/Aegon_II_Targaryen.svg/32px-Aegon_II_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"32\" height=\"35\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/e1/Aegon_II_Targaryen.svg/48px-Aegon_II_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/e1/Aegon_II_Targaryen.svg/64px-Aegon_II_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <b><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">House Targaryen</a>/<a href=\"/index.php/Greens\" title=\"Greens\">Greens</a></b>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Rosby\" title=\"House Rosby\"><img alt=\"House Rosby.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/e8/House_Rosby.svg/20px-House_Rosby.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/e8/House_Rosby.svg/30px-House_Rosby.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/e8/House_Rosby.svg/40px-House_Rosby.svg.png 2x\" /></a>&#160;<a href=\"/index.php/House_Rosby\" title=\"House Rosby\">House Rosby</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Stokeworth\" title=\"House Stokeworth\"><img alt=\"House Stokeworth.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/37/House_Stokeworth.svg/20px-House_Stokeworth.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/37/House_Stokeworth.svg/30px-House_Stokeworth.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/37/House_Stokeworth.svg/40px-House_Stokeworth.svg.png 2x\" /></a>&#160;<a href=\"/index.php/House_Stokeworth\" title=\"House Stokeworth\">House Stokeworth</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Darklyn\" title=\"House Darklyn\"><img alt=\"House Darklyn.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/2/28/House_Darklyn.svg/20px-House_Darklyn.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/2/28/House_Darklyn.svg/30px-House_Darklyn.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/2/28/House_Darklyn.svg/40px-House_Darklyn.svg.png 2x\" /></a>&#160;<a href=\"/index.php/House_Darklyn\" title=\"House Darklyn\">House Darklyn</a></li></ul></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center;\"><b>Commanders</b></td></tr><tr><td width=\"50%\" style=\"border-right:1px dotted #aaa;\"><div class=\"plainlist\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Staunton\" title=\"House Staunton\"><img alt=\"House Staunton.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/9e/House_Staunton.svg/20px-House_Staunton.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/9e/House_Staunton.svg/30px-House_Staunton.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/9/9e/House_Staunton.svg/40px-House_Staunton.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Staunton\" title=\"Lord Staunton\">Lord Staunton</a>†</li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/20px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/30px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/40px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aemon)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Aemon)\">Rhaenys Targaryen</a>†</li></ul>\n</div></td>\n    <td width=\"50%\">                                      <div class=\"plainlist\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\"><img alt=\"Kingsguard.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/20px-Kingsguard.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/30px-Kingsguard.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/40px-Kingsguard.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Criston_Cole\" title=\"Criston Cole\">Criston Cole</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\"><img alt=\"Aegon II Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/e1/Aegon_II_Targaryen.svg/20px-Aegon_II_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/e1/Aegon_II_Targaryen.svg/30px-Aegon_II_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/e1/Aegon_II_Targaryen.svg/40px-Aegon_II_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II Targaryen</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/20px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/30px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/40px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aemond_Targaryen\" title=\"Aemond Targaryen\">Aemond Targaryen</a></li></ul>\n</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center;\"><b>Strength</b></td></tr><tr><td width=\"50%\" style=\"border-right:1px dotted #aaa;\">Rook's Rest garrison<br /><a href=\"/index.php/Meleys\" title=\"Meleys\">Meleys</a>†</td>\n    <td width=\"50%\">                                      More than 2,400 <a href=\"/index.php/Greens\" title=\"Greens\">greens</a>\n<ul><li>100 <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knights</a></li>\n<li>500 <a href=\"/index.php/Men-at-arms\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Men-at-arms\">men-at-arms</a></li>\n<li>1,800 <a href=\"/index.php/Sellsword\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sellsword\">sellswords</a></li>\n<li>added forces from <a href=\"/index.php/Rosby\" title=\"Rosby\">Rosby</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Stokeworth\" title=\"Stokeworth\">Stokeworth</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Duskendale\" title=\"Duskendale\">Duskendale</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Sunfyre\" title=\"Sunfyre\">Sunfyre</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Vhagar\" title=\"Vhagar\">Vhagar</a></li></ul></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center;\"><b>Casualties</b></td></tr><tr><td width=\"50%\" style=\"border-right:1px dotted #aaa;\">100 <a href=\"/index.php/Blacks\" title=\"Blacks\">blacks</a><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Staunton\" title=\"Lord Staunton\">Lord Staunton</a>†<br /><a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aemon)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Aemon)\">Rhaenys Targaryen</a>†<br /><a href=\"/index.php/Meleys\" title=\"Meleys\">Meleys</a>†</td>\n    <td width=\"50%\">                                      800 <a href=\"/index.php/Greens\" title=\"Greens\">greens</a><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II Targaryen</a> (injured)<br /><a href=\"/index.php/Sunfyre\" title=\"Sunfyre\">Sunfyre</a> (injured)</td></tr>\n</tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>A <b>battle at Rook's Rest</b> took place in the <a href=\"/index.php/Crownlands\" title=\"Crownlands\">crownlands</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Prelude\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Prelude</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Battle\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Battle</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Aftermath\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Aftermath</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Prelude\">Prelude</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Battle_at_Rook%27s_Rest&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Prelude\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Criston_Cole\" title=\"Criston Cole\">Criston Cole</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Commander_of_the_Kingsguard\" title=\"Lord Commander of the Kingsguard\">Lord Commander of the Kingsguard</a> and the new <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II Targaryen</a>, devised a more aggressive strategy for the <a href=\"/index.php/Greens\" title=\"Greens\">greens</a> than his predecessor as Hand, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Otto_Hightower\" title=\"Otto Hightower\">Otto Hightower</a>. Criston planned a trap for the <a href=\"/index.php/Blacks\" title=\"Blacks\">blacks</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Rook%27s_Rest\" title=\"Rook&#39;s Rest\">Rook's Rest</a>, while also forcing the submission of the nearby <a href=\"/index.php/Crownlands\" title=\"Crownlands\">crownlands</a> houses that were allied with Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Criston Cole marched out of <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> with 100 <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knights</a>, 500 <a href=\"/index.php/Men-at-arms\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Men-at-arms\">men-at-arms</a>, and three times as many <a href=\"/index.php/Sellsword\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sellsword\">sellswords</a>: thus about 2,400 in total. <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Rosby\" title=\"Lord Rosby\">Lord Rosby</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Stokeworth\" title=\"Lord Stokeworth\">Lord Stokeworth</a> had recently submitted to Aegon to avoid execution in King's Landing, and Criston forced them to prove their loyalty by adding the strength of <a href=\"/index.php/Rosby\" title=\"Rosby\">Rosby</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Stokeworth\" title=\"Stokeworth\">Stokeworth</a> to the green host. Thus augmented, the army advanced upon <a href=\"/index.php/Duskendale\" title=\"Duskendale\">Duskendale</a>. The walled harbor town was caught completely by surprise and unprepared, and quickly fell to Aegon II's forces and <a href=\"/index.php/Sack_of_Duskendale\" title=\"Sack of Duskendale\">was sacked</a>. Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Gunthor_Darklyn\" title=\"Gunthor Darklyn\">Gunthor Darklyn</a> was beheaded for <a href=\"/index.php/Treason\" title=\"Treason\">treason</a>, and most of his <a href=\"/index.php/Household_knight\" title=\"Household knight\">household knights</a> swore their swords to Aegon, although a few chose death.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Staunton\" title=\"Lord Staunton\">Lord Staunton</a> had been forewarned of the approach of Ser Criston's army. He closed the gates of Rook's Rest, but was unable to prevent Criston from burning his fields or killing his <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">smallfolk</a> and livestock. When supplies in Rook's Rest began to run low, Lord Staunton asked for assistance from Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a>, sending a <a href=\"/index.php/Raven\" title=\"Raven\">raven</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tleft\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:502px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Rook%27s_Rest_map.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/f8/Rook%27s_Rest_map.png/500px-Rook%27s_Rest_map.png\" width=\"500\" height=\"324\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/f/f8/Rook%27s_Rest_map.png 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Rook%27s_Rest_map.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Battle at Rook's Rest map</div></div></div><div style=\"clear:left;\"></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Battle\">Battle</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Battle_at_Rook%27s_Rest&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Battle\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:The_Battle_at_Rook%27s_Rest_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/0/0d/The_Battle_at_Rook%27s_Rest_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg/350px-The_Battle_at_Rook%27s_Rest_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"350\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/0/0d/The_Battle_at_Rook%27s_Rest_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg/525px-The_Battle_at_Rook%27s_Rest_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/0/0d/The_Battle_at_Rook%27s_Rest_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg/700px-The_Battle_at_Rook%27s_Rest_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:The_Battle_at_Rook%27s_Rest_by_Jota_Saraiva.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Vhagar\" title=\"Vhagar\">Vhagar</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Sunfyre\" title=\"Sunfyre\">Sunfyre</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Meleys\" title=\"Meleys\">Meleys</a> fight in the Battle at Rook's Rest. Art by Jota Saraiva ©</div></div></div>\n<p>Queen Rhaenyra's sons, <a href=\"/index.php/Jacaerys_Velaryon\" title=\"Jacaerys Velaryon\">Jacaerys</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Joffrey_Velaryon\" title=\"Joffrey Velaryon\">Joffrey Velaryon</a>, were eager to join the fight atop their <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragons</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Vermax\" title=\"Vermax\">Vermax</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Tyraxes\" title=\"Tyraxes\">Tyraxes</a>, but she forbade them to go. Instead, nine days after Staunton's message, <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aemon)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Aemon)\">Rhaenys Targaryen</a>, the Queen Who Never Was, and her <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragon</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Meleys\" title=\"Meleys\">Meleys</a>, the Red Queen, arrived alone above Rook's Rest to aid Lord Staunton. However, Criston was prepared, and had his archers and scorpions fire at Meleys. The dragon was largely unharmed by these attacks, and she responded by burning Criston's soldiers with <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonfire\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dragonfire\">dragonfire</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Criston Cole then sprung his trap. King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II Targaryen</a> and his brother, Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aemond_Targaryen\" title=\"Aemond Targaryen\">Aemond</a>, appeared in the sky atop their own dragons, <a href=\"/index.php/Sunfyre\" title=\"Sunfyre\">Sunfyre</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Vhagar\" title=\"Vhagar\">Vhagar</a>, and attacked Rhaenys and Meleys. The three dragons fought a thousand feet above the field. When Meleys closed her jaws around Sunfyre's neck, Vhagar fell upon them from above, causing the three dragons to crash into to the ground. Although Aemond and Vhagar rose unscathed, Meleys was broken and ripped to pieces from the fall, and Sunfyre had one wing half torn from his body. Aegon suffered severe burns and broken bones. The blackened body of Rhaenys was found beside the carcass of her dragon.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Aemond, Criston, and the surviving greens took Rook's Rest, and killed Lord Staunton and his garrison of one hundred soldiers.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Aftermath\">Aftermath</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Battle_at_Rook%27s_Rest&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Aftermath\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Death_of_Rhaenys.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/97/Death_of_Rhaenys.png/350px-Death_of_Rhaenys.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"519\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/97/Death_of_Rhaenys.png/525px-Death_of_Rhaenys.png 1.5x, /images/9/97/Death_of_Rhaenys.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Death_of_Rhaenys.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The bodies of Rhaenys and Meleys, as depicted by Douglas Wheatley in <i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>.</div></div></div>\n<p>The heads of <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Staunton\" title=\"Lord Staunton\">Lord Staunton</a> and Meleys were taken to <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>. The <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">smallfolk</a> of the city were greatly awed by the sight of the dragon's head, drawn through the city on a cart. Thousands of people left the city, until Dowager Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Alicent_Hightower\" title=\"Alicent Hightower\">Alicent Hightower</a> ordered the gates closed and barred.\n</p><p>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Criston_Cole\" title=\"Criston Cole\">Criston Cole</a> lost eight hundred soldiers to Meleys's dragonfire. King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II Targaryen</a> was incapacitated by his burns for a year; Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aemond_Targaryen\" title=\"Aemond Targaryen\">Aemond Targaryen</a> became <a href=\"/index.php/Regent\" title=\"Regent\">regent</a> while his brother recovered. Aegon's injured dragon, <a href=\"/index.php/Sunfyre\" title=\"Sunfyre\">Sunfyre</a>, was flightless and too heavy to be moved, so was left behind in the fields of Rook's Rest to eat carcasses and livestock.\n</p><p>The loss of <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aemon)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Aemon)\">Rhaenys Targaryen</a> and her dragon, <a href=\"/index.php/Meleys\" title=\"Meleys\">Meleys</a>, was a severe blow to the <a href=\"/index.php/Blacks\" title=\"Blacks\">blacks</a>. Rhaenys's husband, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Corlys_Velaryon\" title=\"Corlys Velaryon\">Corlys Velaryon</a>, was enraged, and blamed her death on Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a>, stating that if the queen or her sons had gone with their dragons, his wife might be alive.\n</p><p>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Walys_Mooton\" title=\"Walys Mooton\">Walys Mooton</a> later led the <a href=\"/index.php/Retaking_of_Rook%27s_Rest\" title=\"Retaking of Rook&#39;s Rest\">retaking of Rook's Rest</a> for the blacks, but was slain in a failed attempt to kill Sunfyre.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Battle_at_Rook%27s_Rest&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Season5Dance_of_Dragons7.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/c/cd/Season5Dance_of_Dragons7.png/350px-Season5Dance_of_Dragons7.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"201\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/c/cd/Season5Dance_of_Dragons7.png/525px-Season5Dance_of_Dragons7.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/c/cd/Season5Dance_of_Dragons7.png/700px-Season5Dance_of_Dragons7.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Season5Dance_of_Dragons7.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aemon)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Aemon)\">Rhaenys Targaryen</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Meleys\" title=\"Meleys\">Meleys</a> fight in the Battle at Rook's Rest, as depicted in <i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"Game of Thrones\">Game of Thrones</a></i>: <i>Histories &amp; Lore</i></div></div></div>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Nine days after <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Staunton\" title=\"Lord Staunton\">Lord Staunton</a> dispatched his plea for help, the sound of leathern wings was heard across the sea, and the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragon</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Meleys\" title=\"Meleys\">Meleys</a> appeared above <a href=\"/index.php/Rook%27s_Rest\" title=\"Rook&#39;s Rest\">Rook's Rest</a>. The Red Queen, she was called, for the scarlet scales that covered her. The membranes of her wings were pink, her crest, horns, and claws bright as <a href=\"/index.php/Copper\" title=\"Copper\">copper</a>. And on her back, in <a href=\"/index.php/Steel\" title=\"Steel\">steel</a> and copper armor that flashed in the sun, rode <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aemon)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Aemon)\">Rhaenys Targaryen</a>, the Queen Who Never Was.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;writings of <a href=\"/index.php/Gyldayn\" title=\"Gyldayn\">Gyldayn</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Criston_Cole\" title=\"Criston Cole\">Criston Cole</a> had sprung his trap, and <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aemon)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Aemon)\">Rhaenys</a> had come snatching at the bait. Now the teeth closed round her.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;writings of <a href=\"/index.php/Gyldayn\" title=\"Gyldayn\">Gyldayn</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aemon)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Aemon)\">Rhaenys</a> made no attempt to flee. With a glad cry and a crack of her whip, she turned <a href=\"/index.php/Meleys\" title=\"Meleys\">Meleys</a> toward the foe.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;writings of <a href=\"/index.php/Gyldayn\" title=\"Gyldayn\">Gyldayn</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Beloved daughter of Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Jocelyn_Baratheon\" title=\"Jocelyn Baratheon\">Jocelyn Baratheon</a> and Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aemon_Targaryen_(son_of_Jaehaerys_I)\" title=\"Aemon Targaryen (son of Jaehaerys I)\">Aemon Targaryen</a>, faithful wife to Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Corlys_Velaryon\" title=\"Corlys Velaryon\">Corlys Velaryon</a>, mother and grandmother, the Queen Who Never Was lived fearlessly, and died amidst blood and fire. She was fifty-five years old.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;writings of <a href=\"/index.php/Gyldayn\" title=\"Gyldayn\">Gyldayn</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>It should have been you. <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Staunton\" title=\"Lord Staunton\">Staunton</a> sent to you, yet you left it to <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aemon)\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen (daughter of Aemon)\">my wife</a> to answer and forbade <a href=\"/index.php/Jacaerys_Velaryon\" title=\"Jacaerys Velaryon\">your</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Joffrey_Velaryon\" title=\"Joffrey Velaryon\">sons</a> to join her.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Corlys_Velaryon\" title=\"Corlys Velaryon\">Corlys Velaryon</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Battle_at_Rook%27s_Rest&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div cla